Got it ✅ Let’s go step by step very clearly so you can make a wish link on GitHub Pages.


---

🎂 How to Create a Birthday Wish Link on GitHub

🔹 Step 1: Create a GitHub Account

1. Go to github.com


2. Click Sign up (if you don’t already have an account).


3. Verify your email → Log in.




---

🔹 Step 2: Create a Repository

1. On the top right, click the + sign → New repository.


2. Repository name → type: wish-link (you can choose any name).


3. Select Public.


4. Tick ✅ Add a README file.


5. Click Create repository.




---

🔹 Step 3: Add Your HTML File

1. Go to your new repository.


2. Click Add file → Create new file.


3. In the filename box, type: index.html.


4. Paste this code:



<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Special Wish</title>
  <style>
    body {
      text-align: center;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffcc70, #ff7eb3);
      color: #fff;
      padding: 50px;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5em;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    p {
      font-size: 1.2em;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1 id="greeting">Happy Birthday!</h1>
  <p id="message">Wishing you joy and happiness 🎉</p>

  <script>
    const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    const name = params.get('n') || "Friend";
    const type = params.get('t') || "birthday";

    let greeting = "";
    if (type === "birthday") {
      greeting = `🎂 Happy Birthday, ${name}! 🎉`;
    } else if (type === "anniversary") {
      greeting = `💖 Happy Anniversary, ${name}! 💍`;
    } else {
      greeting = `🌟 Hello ${name}, best wishes to you!`;
    }

    document.getElementById("greeting").textContent = greeting;
  </script>
</body>
</html>

5. Scroll down → Click Commit new file (save).




---

🔹 Step 4: Enable GitHub Pages

1. In your repository, click Settings (top menu).


2. On the left, scroll down → click Pages.


3. Under Source, select:

Branch: main

Folder: / (root)

Click Save.



4. Wait 1–2 minutes.


5. You’ll get a live link like:

https://yourusername.github.io/wish-link/




---

🔹 Step 5: Test & Share Your Wish Link

Now, add names and types to the URL:

🎂 Birthday:

https://yourusername.github.io/wish-link/?n=Priyanka&t=birthday

💖 Anniversary:

https://yourusername.github.io/wish-link/?n=Rahul&t=anniversary

🌟 General:

https://yourusername.github.io/wish-link/?n=Friend&t=general

Each link will automatically show a personalized message 🎉


